CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 10, 1965, pg. 5, reads: "WORKSHOP GUESTS - Some of the celebrated guests who enjoyed the workshop are (left to right) Fr. Michael Williams of the CYO; Phyl Garland, Courier writer; George Wein, producer of the Newport Jazz Festival, jazz impresario and producer of the upcoming Pittsburgh Jazz Festival; Hazel Garland, Pittsburgh Courier theatrical writer, and columnist; Walt Harper and the celebrated 'jazz priest' of Boston, Mass., Fr. O'Connor, who is also heard over the 'Voice of America' radio program, broadcast over the world. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Father Michael Williams, Phyliss Garland, George Wein, Hazel Garland, Walt Harper, and "jazz priest" Father Norman J. O'Connor, posed around table in restaurant with mural of Greco-Roman ruins on wall, for planning meeting of Hilton Jazz Workshop
